a:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 mb-6 not-prose","children":["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-2.5 border-l-4 border-yellow-400/50 pl-4","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"NAND flash prices jump 50% in a single day"}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Phison pivots to enterprise as supply chain buckles"}]]}],["$","li","2",{"className":"flex items-start gap-2.5 leading-snug","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-0.5 text-base flex-shrink-0 animate-pulse","style":{"color":"#f5c518","textShadow":"0 0 8px #f5c518, 0 0 18px #f5a500aa"},"children":"★"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xl italic text-text-primary","children":"Consumers may face SSD price hikes within months"}]]}]]}]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["A 50% overnight price hike isn’t just a blip—it’s a supply chain emergency. ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.tomshardware.com/news/phison-nand-flash-prices-increase-50-percent","children":"Phison’s CEO"}]," confirmed the spike in NAND flash prices, a critical component for SSDs, smartphones, and data centers. The cause? A perfect storm of constrained supply and surging demand, particularly from AI server farms and enterprise storage upgrades. Phison, a major player in SSD controllers, is now scrambling to bulk up inventory while warning that ",["$","em",null,{"children":"both cash and stockpiles are running low"}],".\nThis isn’t just a manufacturer’s problem. The ripple effects hit three groups hardest: ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"enterprise buyers"}]," facing delayed upgrades, ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"PC builders"}]," watching SSD prices creep upward, and ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"consumer electronics brands"}]," already squeezing margins on laptops and phones. The ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.anandtech.com/show/21234/the-nand-flash-shortage-explained","children":"current NAND shortage"}]," echoes 2021’s chaos—but this time, AI’s insatiable appetite for storage is the wild card.\nPhison’s pivot toward enterprise customers is telling. When a controller specialist starts prioritizing data centers over consumer SSDs, it signals where the money (and desperation) lies. The question isn’t ",["$","em",null,{"children":"if"}]," this will trickle down to retail prices, but ",["$","em",null,{"children":"how fast"}],"—and whether budget drives will disappear first."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-4 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/nand-prices-spike-50-overnightwho-pays-the-real-co/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Kada skladišni čipovi postanu luksuz, tko će platiti račun?","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"Kada skladišni čipovi postanu luksuz, tko će platiti račun?"}]]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["For users, the practical impact is immediate: ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"expect SSD deals to dry up"}],". Retailers like ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.newegg.com/","children":"Newegg"}]," and ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.amazon.com/","children":"Amazon"}]," are already adjusting listings, with entry-level 1TB drives inching toward $80–$90—up from $60 just months ago. The pain will hit hardest for ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"content creators"}]," relying on high-capacity storage and ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"gamers"}]," eyeing PCIe 5.0 upgrades. Even cloud services may pass costs along, with ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/storage/","children":"AWS and Google Cloud"}]," quietly revising storage pricing tiers.\nThe industry’s response is fragmented. Samsung and SK Hynix are ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.reuters.com/technology/samsung-electronics-q2-profit-likely-fell-96-y-y-2024-07-05/","children":"ramping up production"}],", but new fab capacity takes 12–18 months. Meanwhile, smaller players like ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.westerndigital.com/","children":"Western Digital"}]," and ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.micron.com/","children":"Micron"}]," face a brutal choice: absorb losses or risk losing market share. Regulators are watching, too—",["$","strong",null,{"children":"price-fixing accusations"}]," lurk whenever shortages get this severe.\nThe real test comes in Q4. If NAND prices stay elevated, holiday tech sales could look very different: fewer discounts, more ‘out of stock’ notices, and a quiet shift toward ","$L13",". That’s not progress—that’s a step backward."]}]]}]
